{"id":14881126,"mediaExerciseId":"12bc9739-91b6-4e14-a857-9b27042801ca","exerciseName":"7","chapterName":"8","chapterTitle":"Stock Valuation","groupId":612321,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":266,"solutions":[{"id":6050103,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we have to find out the **current share price.**\n\nIt is a fundamental principle in which each cash flow is discounted to its present value. We should be familiar with the cash flow formula and discounting. The present value of the stock is equal to the sum of all discounted cash flows. Over $13$ years, the corporation no longer pays divided dividends, and all dividends paid are now constant.\n\n As a consequence, there would be no such thing as a terminal value. Several times, a terminal value is stated, that should be taken into account and discounted to present value.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Next, let's see the general case model formula for the calculation.\n \n\n$$\\begin{align*}\nP_0&=\\frac{D_1}{(1+R)^1} + \\frac{D_2}{(1+R)^2} + \\frac{D_3}{(1+R)^3} + \\frac{D_4}{(1+R)^4} + \\frac{D_5}{(1+R)^5}\\\\[12pt]&\\phantom{+} + \\frac{D_6}{(1+R)^6} + \\frac{D_7}{(1+R)^7} + \\frac{D_8}{(1+R)^8} + \\frac{D_9}{(1+R)^9} + \\frac{D_{10}}{(1+R)^{10}} \\\\[12pt]&\\phantom{+} + \\frac{D_{11}}{(1+R)^{11}} + \\frac{D_{12}}{(1+R)^{12}} + \\frac{D_{13}}{(1+R)^{13}}&&&(1)\n\\end{align*}$$\n\nwhere:\n\n* $P_0$ is the current share price,\n\n*  $D_1, D_2, D_3......$ is the future dividend,\n\n* $R$ is the  required return.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"We have the following information.\n\n* The future dividend is equal to $\\$8.25$\n\n* The required return is equal to $11.2\\%.$\n\nNow, let's do the calculation according to the formula which we denote with $(1)$. \n\n\n\n$$\\begin{align*}\nP_0&=\\frac{D_1}{(1+R)^1} + \\frac{D_2}{(1+R)^2} + \\frac{D_3}{(1+R)^3} + \\frac{D_4}{(1+R)^4} + \\frac{D_5}{(1+R)^5}\\\\[12pt]&\\phantom{+} + \\frac{D_6}{(1+R)^6} + \\frac{D_7}{(1+R)^7} + \\frac{D_8}{(1+R)^8} + \\frac{D_9}{(1+R)^9} + \\frac{D_{10}}{(1+R)^{10}} \\\\[12pt]&\\phantom{+} + \\frac{D_{11}}{(1+R)^{11}} + \\frac{D_{12}}{(1+R)^{12}} + \\frac{D_{13}}{(1+R)^{13}} \\\\[12pt]\n&=\\frac{\\$8.25}{(1+0.112)^1} + \\frac{\\$8.25}{(1+0.112)^2} + \\frac{\\$8.25}{(1+0.112)^3} + \\frac{\\$8.25}{(1+0.112)^4} \\\\[12pt]&\\phantom{+} + \\frac{\\$8.25}{(1+0.112)^5} + \\frac{\\$8.25}{(1+0.112)^6} + \\frac{\\$8.25}{(1+0.112)^7} + \\frac{\\$8.25}{(1+0.112)^8}\\\\[12pt]&\\phantom{+} + \\frac{\\$8.25}{(1+0.112)^9}  + \\frac{\\$8.25}{(1+0.112)^{10}}  + \\frac{\\$8.25}{(1+0.112)^{11}} + \\frac{\\$8.25}{(1+0.112)^{12}} \\\\[12pt]&\\phantom{+}+ \\frac{\\$8.25}{(1+0.112)^{13}} \\\\[12pt]\n&=\\$7.41+\\$6.67+\\$5.99+\\$5.39+\\$4.85+\\$4.36+ \\$3.92\\\\[12pt]&\\phantom{+} + \\$3.52+\\$3.17+\\$2.85+\\$2.56+\\$2.30+\\$2.07\\\\[12pt]\n&=\\$55.06.\n\\end{align*}$$\n\nTherefore, we can conclude that the current share price is $P_0 =\\$55.06.$ ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"$\\boxed{\\$55.06.}$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":true,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"a6661ab3-0d37-4fca-aa71-de549cd05bf8","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957"